1
00:00:07,933 --> 00:00:12,133
♪I've braved the storms, walked through the rain♪

2
00:00:12,167 --> 00:00:15,533
♪Seen the highs and lows along the way♪

3
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:18,933
♪But you stay quiet, never change♪

4
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:22,533
♪Like a child who dreams beneath the stars♪

5
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:25,933
♪I've read the story in your eyes♪

6
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:29,433
♪And finally, nothing's left to hide♪

7
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:33,033
♪You won't give in to a world so cold♪

8
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:36,633
♪So you wander through it on your own♪

9
00:00:36,767 --> 00:00:40,233
♪Maybe fate has drawn us near♪

10
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:43,233
♪Just to help you learn to believe♪

11
00:00:43,467 --> 00:00:46,400
♪Everything you've questioned deep inside♪

12
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:50,633
♪I'll be the proof you need♪

13
00:00:50,767 --> 00:00:52,067
♪I've made my choice♪

14
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:55,033
♪For you, I'll be brave and break the rules♪

15
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:58,267
♪What's there to fear even if the world is right and I am wrong?♪

16
00:00:58,967 --> 00:01:01,833
♪One day, all of this will turn into memories♪

17
00:01:02,367 --> 00:01:05,267
♪Every storm we faced will turn into our life's scenery♪

18
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:08,933
♪For you, I'll be brave and break the rules♪

19
00:01:09,233 --> 00:01:12,167
♪What's there to fear even if the world is right and I am wrong?♪

20
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:15,733
♪Even if, in the end, the whole world turns against me♪

21
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:19,167
♪I won't regret having loved you♪

22
00:01:19,267 --> 00:01:22,833
♪With all my heart♪

23
00:01:23,067 --> 00:01:26,667
♪I've held you close♪

24
00:01:26,767 --> 00:01:30,367
♪Walked by your side♪

25
00:01:30,533 --> 00:01:34,833
♪And loved the fire that burned inside you♪

26
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,367
[The First Frost]

27
00:01:36,367 --> 00:01:37,867
[Adapted from the novel of the same name by Zhu Yi]

28
00:01:41,867 --> 00:01:43,300
Sang Yan fought another student

29
00:01:43,467 --> 00:01:44,833
for Wen Yifan.

30
00:01:45,367 --> 00:01:46,600
As for the fight

31
00:01:46,967 --> 00:01:48,233
we've already settled it

32
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:49,200
with the injured student.

33
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:50,767
Now, what we need to handle

34
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:54,233
is the issue of your early romance.

35
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,667
We're not in a relationship.

36
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:00,400
That's right.

37
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,167
We're not in an early relationship.

38
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:04,567
My feelings for Wen Yifan

39
00:02:05,133 --> 00:02:06,133
are one-sided.

40
00:02:09,033 --> 00:02:10,967
Teenagers often have fantasies about love.

41
00:02:10,967 --> 00:02:12,133
I understand that.

42
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:14,200
But you have such heavy schoolwork now.

43
00:02:14,567 --> 00:02:16,267
You'll definitely get distracted by early romance.

44
00:02:19,133 --> 00:02:20,333
Sang Yan

45
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:21,733
can you turn your passion

46
00:02:21,733 --> 00:02:23,567
into motivation for hard work?

47
00:02:23,733 --> 00:02:25,633
You'll mature in university

48
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,133
and there's plenty of time for dating then.

49
00:02:27,333 --> 00:02:28,167
That's right.

50
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:29,267
Yes.

51
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:30,333
That's right.

52
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:35,133
Yifan's uncle

53
00:02:35,167 --> 00:02:36,667
you really should pay more attention.

54
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:38,533
You should care more about her.

55
00:02:38,933 --> 00:02:39,667
Okay.

56
00:02:45,767 --> 00:02:46,467
Alright, it's no big deal.

57
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:47,600
You can communicate.

58
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:48,300
That's it.

59
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:49,133
I'm off to class.

60
00:02:50,433 --> 00:02:51,167
Stand properly.

61
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:52,600
The teacher was explaining so well!

62
00:02:53,067 --> 00:02:54,133
Thank you, teacher.

63
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,533
Have some shame.

64
00:03:08,867 --> 00:03:10,200
How can you be so shameless?

65
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:11,100
At such a young age

66
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:13,133
you've already learned how to seduce men?

67
00:03:14,367 --> 00:03:15,767
You need to focus on your studies!

68
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:17,100
You...

69
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:18,200
You startled me.

70
00:03:19,667 --> 00:03:20,900
You really like her?

71
00:03:22,733 --> 00:03:24,367
Is that even a question?

72
00:03:24,467 --> 00:03:25,533
Son, well done.

73
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:26,667
Good taste.

74
00:03:26,667 --> 00:03:28,100
You've got the same taste as me.

75
00:03:30,133 --> 00:03:31,467
Even if you like her, just bear with it.

76
00:03:32,467 --> 00:03:33,767
Wait until university, okay?

77
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:34,767
Right.

78
00:03:44,533 --> 00:03:45,133
Let's go!

79
00:03:45,733 --> 00:03:46,300
Go home!

80
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,900
Go home and pack your things!

81
00:03:48,067 --> 00:03:48,733
Did you hear me?

82
00:03:50,167 --> 00:03:51,433
Why do I need to pack my things?

83
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:54,033
Well, your aunt's brother

84
00:03:54,033 --> 00:03:55,567
has a house in Beiyu.

85
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:56,867
We're planning to move there.

86
00:04:03,667 --> 00:04:04,433
Listen

87
00:04:04,667 --> 00:04:05,467
after transferring schools

88
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:06,900
you have to completely sever ties

89
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:07,900
with this guy!

90
00:04:08,067 --> 00:04:08,867
Did you hear me?

91
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,533
Goodbye.

92
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:30,600
[Episode 7]
[A Secret...]

93
00:04:36,533 --> 00:04:38,467
[3085 Days]

94
00:04:38,467 --> 00:04:40,233
[Cutting Room]

95
00:04:40,233 --> 00:04:44,067
[23rd Day of Living Together Officially]

96
00:04:53,867 --> 00:04:57,833
[Sang Yan]

97
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:58,833
What time are you on duty until?

98
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,067
[Wen Yifan]

99
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:02,100
I'm about to finish work.

100
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:02,700
What's up?

101
00:05:04,933 --> 00:05:06,367
[Sang Yan]

102
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:08,500
Could you help me pick up a pizza on your way?

103
00:05:10,033 --> 00:05:10,900
Someone wants it.

104
00:05:15,033 --> 00:05:16,167
Why doesn't he just order takeout?

105
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,133
Eating pizza during the New Year?

106
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,700
Is it because his girlfriend wants it?

107
00:05:26,033 --> 00:05:27,100
Pick your favorite flavor.

108
00:05:29,767 --> 00:05:31,333
Isn't what you're doing a bit scummy?

109
00:05:40,467 --> 00:05:44,167
[Pizza Hut]

110
00:05:46,967 --> 00:05:48,067
Why are so many people

111
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,833
eating pizza during the New Year holiday?

112
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:07,567
Why isn't it Duan Jiaxu?

113
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:09,633
There's no Duan Jiaxu here.

114
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:14,200
This is my roommate.

115
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:16,833
Roommate?

116
00:06:17,700 --> 00:06:18,400
Female roommate?

117
00:06:23,567 --> 00:06:24,533
You two are sleeping together?

118
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:25,967
We live in two rooms...

119
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:27,733
We live in two rooms.

120
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,300
We just share this apartment.

121
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:32,833
I knew it!

122
00:06:33,067 --> 00:06:34,300
You're so pretty

123
00:06:34,533 --> 00:06:35,733
and my brother's so ugly.

124
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:37,333
You two could only be ordinary roommates.

125
00:06:38,033 --> 00:06:39,167
Miss, my name is Sang Zhi.

126
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:40,067
I'm his sister.

127
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,100
My name is Wen Yifan.

128
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,067
Miss, let me do it.

129
00:06:42,933 --> 00:06:43,533
Thank you.

130
00:06:43,967 --> 00:06:45,067
Sorry for the trouble.

131
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,100
My mom won't let me eat Pizza at home.

132
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,933
So I had to come here to satisfy my cravings.

133
00:06:49,133 --> 00:06:50,967
Who eats pizza during the New Year holiday?

134
00:06:51,533 --> 00:06:52,133
Mind your business.

135
00:06:53,533 --> 00:06:54,967
There really are a lot of people.

136
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:56,833
I waited half an hour to get this.

137
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:04,967
Eat up.

138
00:07:05,033 --> 00:07:06,267
After you're done, go study.

139
00:07:07,267 --> 00:07:08,567
You're still studying during the New Year holiday?

140
00:07:08,967 --> 00:07:09,833
I'm in my senior year.

141
00:07:11,633 --> 00:07:13,467
You came here because it was too noisy to study at home

142
00:07:13,467 --> 00:07:14,767
with all the relatives around?

143
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:16,367
What relatives?

144
00:07:16,467 --> 00:07:17,500
It's very quiet at home.

145
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:19,100
It's just me and my parents at home.

146
00:07:19,367 --> 00:07:20,567
My brother's not coming back.

147
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:23,133
It feels pretty lonely.

148
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:31,500
Shouldn't you be back after the 8th day of New Year?

149
00:07:32,267 --> 00:07:33,767
There are too many relatives at home.

150
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:34,533
We don't have enough room.

151
00:07:42,133 --> 00:07:42,767
Miss

152
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:45,433
were you my brother's classmate...

153
00:07:50,333 --> 00:07:51,300
in high school?

154
00:07:53,267 --> 00:07:54,267
Do you remember me?

155
00:07:54,367 --> 00:07:55,467
Of course I remember.

156
00:07:55,667 --> 00:07:56,833
You're the prettiest

157
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:59,133
of my brother's female classmates.

158
00:07:59,633 --> 00:08:00,967
I was just focusing on food earlier

159
00:08:00,967 --> 00:08:01,933
and didn't recognize you immediately.

160
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:03,900
You're getting prettier too.

161
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:05,367
Miss, do you remember me?

162
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:06,500
Yes.

163
00:08:07,467 --> 00:08:08,767
Do you remember?

164
00:08:08,767 --> 00:08:09,833
When you were very young

165
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:11,133
you once got lost?

166
00:08:11,133 --> 00:08:12,733
Later, you asked me to help you find your brother.

167
00:08:12,933 --> 00:08:14,500
You even promised to treat me to ice cream.

168
00:08:15,633 --> 00:08:16,733
Oh, I remember.

169
00:08:17,067 --> 00:08:18,267
I didn't get lost at that time.

170
00:08:18,467 --> 00:08:19,700
But my brother said I was lost

171
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:20,967
so I had to be lost.

172
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:54,233
What's wrong?

173
00:08:55,933 --> 00:08:56,867
Miss

174
00:08:57,567 --> 00:08:59,700
I can't find my brother.

175
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:13,133
Is your brother

176
00:09:13,233 --> 00:09:14,333
from our school?

177
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:15,633
Yes.

178
00:09:16,733 --> 00:09:18,733
He asked me to wait for him at the overpass.

179
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:21,500
The overpass...

180
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:22,267
is over there.

181
00:09:22,267 --> 00:09:23,133
I'll take you there.

182
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:24,500
Thank you, Miss.

183
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:30,533
Do you remember your brother's phone number?

184
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:32,633
I don't remember it.

185
00:09:34,033 --> 00:09:35,733
What does your brother look like?

186
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:36,533
He...

187
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:37,767
is really handsome.

188
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,333
Everyone likes to play with him.

189
00:10:02,333 --> 00:10:03,667
Which one is your brother?

190
00:10:04,167 --> 00:10:05,367
That one over there.

191
00:10:10,367 --> 00:10:12,033
Didn't I tell you to wait for me here?

192
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:13,667
How would I know this place?

193
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,067
What a coincidence.

194
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:17,067
She's my sister.

195
00:10:19,367 --> 00:10:20,333
I'm going now.

196
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:26,700
Miss, thank you.

197
00:10:26,733 --> 00:10:27,933
Let's eat ice cream together.

198
00:10:32,367 --> 00:10:34,433
If you're free, let's go.

199
00:10:46,633 --> 00:10:48,933
If it weren't for my brother's promise to buy me candy

200
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:50,433
I wouldn't have helped him...

201
00:11:02,133 --> 00:11:03,433
I wouldn't have helped him lie.

202
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:08,267
Let's go, Miss.

203
00:11:08,267 --> 00:11:09,100
Let's go eat pizza.

204
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:09,733
I'm not hungry.

205
00:11:09,733 --> 00:11:10,533
You guys go ahead.

206
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:11,800
By the way

207
00:11:11,967 --> 00:11:13,133
there's a lot of food

208
00:11:13,133 --> 00:11:14,333
in these cabinets

209
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:15,500
and in the fridge.

210
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,633
Take whatever you want.

211
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,133
It's mostly your brother's stuff.

212
00:11:19,933 --> 00:11:20,767
Wait, Miss.

213
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:22,933
How did you end up as my brother's roommate?

214
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,233
Just a coincidence.

215
00:11:29,667 --> 00:11:30,733
It must be fate.

216
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:31,367
Are you eating or not?

217
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:36,333
Hurry up, go eat.

218
00:11:36,433 --> 00:11:37,267
I'm going to work now.

219
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:45,067
You're such a bigmouth.

220
00:12:19,567 --> 00:12:20,367
It's time to eat!

221
00:12:21,267 --> 00:12:22,633
Go bring the other dishes over.

222
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:24,767
Why don't you ask Yifan to join us for dinner?

223
00:12:28,167 --> 00:12:29,367
Aren't you going to invite her?

224
00:12:32,867 --> 00:12:34,533
Since you two are roommates

225
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:35,900
you should get along well.

226
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:40,933
Why are you talking like mom?

227
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,900
Besides, what's it got to do with you?

228
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:44,567
She's been good to me.

229
00:12:44,767 --> 00:12:46,733
She even lets me take whatever I want.

230
00:12:46,733 --> 00:12:48,433
Shouldn't you be polite with her?

231
00:12:48,433 --> 00:12:49,300
She's nice to you

232
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:50,433
but what's it got to do with me?

233
00:12:52,133 --> 00:12:52,967
Invite her yourself.

234
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:53,567
I won't.

235
00:12:54,133 --> 00:12:55,267
She's not my roommate, anyway.

236
00:12:58,400 --> 00:12:59,867
I'm not polite, and you shouldn't be either.

237
00:13:00,933 --> 00:13:01,567
Go.

238
00:13:09,167 --> 00:13:10,067
Miss Yifan.

239
00:13:11,567 --> 00:13:12,233
Please come in.

240
00:13:15,233 --> 00:13:15,933
Miss

241
00:13:16,133 --> 00:13:17,333
my brother made a hotpot.

242
00:13:17,333 --> 00:13:18,667
Come join us.

243
00:13:19,233 --> 00:13:20,333
I'm not hungry. You guys go ahead.

244
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:23,267
Miss, you might not know

245
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:25,567
but my brother and I

246
00:13:25,567 --> 00:13:27,400
can never enjoy a meal alone.

247
00:13:28,633 --> 00:13:29,367
Please.

248
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:36,933
Okay.

249
00:13:42,867 --> 00:13:43,400
Let's go.

250
00:13:48,667 --> 00:13:49,900
Are you hungry again so soon?

251
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:51,133
My brother says

252
00:13:51,133 --> 00:13:53,133
the New Year is all about family reunion, having hotpot.

253
00:13:53,367 --> 00:13:54,367
Miss Yifan, please sit here.

254
00:13:59,167 --> 00:14:00,300
Thank you, Sang Zhi.

255
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:01,967
You can call me by my nickname, Zhi.

256
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:02,900
Zhi?

257
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,133
That's really cute.

258
00:14:06,367 --> 00:14:07,333
What are you laughing at?

259
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:09,067
What's wrong with her saying my nickname is cute?

260
00:14:09,067 --> 00:14:10,433
Doesn't it sound like a maid's name?

261
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:11,667
Your name sounds like a eunuch.

262
00:14:11,667 --> 00:14:13,500
You'd better say that in front of your dad.

263
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,267
Eunuch Yan.

264
00:14:20,733 --> 00:14:21,633
By the way, Zhi

265
00:14:22,067 --> 00:14:23,333
you're about to take the university entrance exam, right?

266
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:25,867
Have you decided which university you want to go to?

267
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,333
Not yet.

268
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:30,967
I'm stuck between Nanwu University and Yihe University.

269
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:31,900
Are you confident about both?

270
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:33,367
Unless something unexpected happens.

271
00:14:33,733 --> 00:14:34,900
So, your grades are good enough.

272
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:37,300
I'm just worried about a bad performance on the exam.

273
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:39,800
No need to worry so much.

274
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,867
And both universities

275
00:14:42,233 --> 00:14:43,133
are pretty good.

276
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:44,533
They each have their own advantages.

277
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:47,233
The only thing is that Yihe is further from Nanwu.

278
00:14:47,433 --> 00:14:49,733
Also, the climate there is different from here.

279
00:14:50,233 --> 00:14:51,700
You should consider this point.

280
00:14:52,867 --> 00:14:54,700
Miss, which university did you graduate from?

281
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:05,800
Yihe University.

282
00:15:07,567 --> 00:15:08,733
No wonder you know so much about it.

283
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:10,433
What's your major?

284
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:12,867
Network and New Media.

285
00:15:13,267 --> 00:15:15,067
Wouldn't Nanwu University be a better choice

286
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:15,900
for this major?

287
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:22,867
If we just talk about this major

288
00:15:22,867 --> 00:15:23,700
actually

289
00:15:24,067 --> 00:15:25,300
Nanwu University's is the better choice.

290
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:27,767
Then why did you choose Yihe University?

291
00:15:40,433 --> 00:15:41,267
What are you looking at me for?

292
00:15:42,533 --> 00:15:43,333
Keep talking.

293
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:48,700
I want to know, too.

294
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,433
What's the reason?

295
00:16:05,700 --> 00:16:08,167
At that time, I didn't plan to apply for this major.

296
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:09,100
Maybe

297
00:16:09,667 --> 00:16:10,433
I misjudged

298
00:16:10,433 --> 00:16:11,633
the cut-off scores

299
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:14,267
so I applied to Yihe University.

300
00:16:23,933 --> 00:16:24,533
I'm full.

301
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:31,067
What's wrong with him?

302
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:32,633
Why is he being so sarcastic?

303
00:16:38,767 --> 00:16:39,767
By the way, Yifan

304
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:41,233
can I ask you something?

305
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:43,267
Did you

306
00:16:43,567 --> 00:16:45,500
ever date my brother?

307
00:16:47,933 --> 00:16:48,533
No.

308
00:16:48,533 --> 00:16:49,900
I heard from my parents

309
00:16:50,033 --> 00:16:51,733
that my brother had an early romance

310
00:16:51,733 --> 00:16:52,767
in high school.

311
00:16:53,233 --> 00:16:53,967
I just remembered.

312
00:16:53,967 --> 00:16:54,500
Little rascal.

313
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:56,067
What's up?

314
00:16:56,767 --> 00:16:58,033
Let's go home.

315
00:16:58,333 --> 00:16:59,533
I just started eating.

316
00:16:59,767 --> 00:17:00,733
I want to stay a bit longer.

317
00:17:00,733 --> 00:17:02,300
Mom and Dad will be home soon.

318
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:03,767
They asked me to escort you back.

319
00:17:04,133 --> 00:17:04,800
Let's go.

320
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:06,067
No, I want to eat more.

321
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:09,133
Eat? Who can eat more than you?

322
00:17:32,767 --> 00:17:33,700
What are you staring at?

323
00:17:33,967 --> 00:17:35,433
Sang Yan, why do I feel

324
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:37,333
like you don't treat Miss Yifan well?

325
00:17:38,133 --> 00:17:39,367
She's nice, isn't she?

326
00:17:39,633 --> 00:17:41,167
She's gentle when she talks.

327
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:42,633
But just based on apparences

328
00:17:42,633 --> 00:17:44,100
you two are worlds apart.

329
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:46,633
With your attitude

330
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:49,133
girls definitely won't like it.

331
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:50,933
What attitude?

332
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:55,333
Girls generally like

333
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:56,633
gentle

334
00:17:56,633 --> 00:17:57,500
good-tempered

335
00:17:57,733 --> 00:17:59,100
attentive

336
00:17:59,100 --> 00:17:59,900
and considerate guys.

337
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:02,433
It's fine if their family situation isn't great.

338
00:18:03,133 --> 00:18:04,433
Like Jiaxu.

339
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:05,100
Who?

340
00:18:05,867 --> 00:18:06,633
Jiaxu.

341
00:18:07,833 --> 00:18:08,500
You're quite knowledgeable, huh?

342
00:18:08,867 --> 00:18:09,700
So

343
00:18:09,933 --> 00:18:11,667
since you don't have the advantage in looks

344
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,733
you need to work harder.

345
00:18:14,133 --> 00:18:15,500
Don't just stay at home

346
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,300
sitting around.

347
00:18:23,933 --> 00:18:26,167
Does your brother have any other job

348
00:18:26,167 --> 00:18:27,367
besides running the restaurant?

349
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:30,067
He did before

350
00:18:30,233 --> 00:18:32,433
but recently, I don't know why, he quit.

351
00:18:33,633 --> 00:18:34,500
Do you also think

352
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:36,133
my brother is a bit idle?

353
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:40,567
Today, she even asked me

354
00:18:40,567 --> 00:18:41,700
about your work.

355
00:19:07,967 --> 00:19:09,433
Why don't you stop at the parking lot?

356
00:19:10,633 --> 00:19:11,567
It's just a few steps.

357
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:12,567
You can go up by yourself.

358
00:19:12,767 --> 00:19:14,000
You're not going home tonight?

359
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,400
Aren't you afraid Mom and Dad will break your legs?

360
00:19:21,133 --> 00:19:22,300
Let me know when you're home.

361
00:19:23,067 --> 00:19:23,733
Transfer the fare to me.

362
00:19:29,567 --> 00:19:30,300
Leaving?

363
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:34,067
I knew you had something going on!

364
00:20:55,833 --> 00:20:59,333
♪The dust of lies and your wounds♪

365
00:20:59,667 --> 00:21:02,967
♪All hide in your eyes♪

366
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:08,533
♪Jot down the wishes you've made before♪

367
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:13,833
♪Will you cherish my heart...♪

368
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:17,067
You didn't go home?

369
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:20,633
It's too noisy at home.

370
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,067
Could it be noisier than here?

371
00:21:25,433 --> 00:21:27,300
When I was little, I loved fireworks.

372
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:30,967
Does your family set off fireworks for the New Year?

373
00:21:32,367 --> 00:21:33,100
Not often.

374
00:21:34,433 --> 00:21:35,567
What about your sister? Doesn't she?

375
00:21:37,067 --> 00:21:38,367
I don't focus on her much.

376
00:21:39,433 --> 00:21:43,067
♪Can you hold me in your freezing night...♪

377
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:45,900
You didn't eat much earlier.

378
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:46,867
Are you hungry?

379
00:21:51,433 --> 00:21:52,500
If you're hungry

380
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:53,433
we can cook...

381
00:21:54,367 --> 00:21:55,167
noodles.

382
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,933
Are you going to cook a whole package again?

383
00:22:09,500 --> 00:22:11,733
They look so happy over there.

384
00:22:12,433 --> 00:22:15,533
♪Fate changes and the confessions come too late♪

385
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:18,800
♪The love that was once absent...♪

386
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,800
[Fifteenth of January, Lantern Festival]

387
00:22:28,233 --> 00:22:29,000
Just a reminder.

388
00:22:29,433 --> 00:22:30,133
In a moment

389
00:22:30,500 --> 00:22:31,633
eat more, talk less.

390
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,200
You got it wrong.

391
00:22:33,933 --> 00:22:35,100
What grandparents like

392
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:36,633
a granddaughter-in-law who eats in silence?

393
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:39,100
I'm afraid you'll spill the beans.

394
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:42,233
After all, my grandparents

395
00:22:42,633 --> 00:22:43,867
aren't just ordinary elderly.

396
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:46,000
How so?

397
00:22:46,333 --> 00:22:48,067
Back then, to chase my grandma

398
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:50,300
my grandpa gave up his family business in Hong Kong

399
00:22:50,767 --> 00:22:51,967
and came to Nanwu alone.

400
00:22:51,967 --> 00:22:53,633
He's seen all kinds of people.

401
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,433
When your grandma was young

402
00:22:55,433 --> 00:22:56,633
she must have been a great beauty.

403
00:22:58,633 --> 00:22:59,200
And not only

404
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:00,067
was she beautiful

405
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,067
but her education was also excellent.

406
00:23:01,300 --> 00:23:03,300
She was very well-known in Hong Kong's banking industry.

407
00:23:03,867 --> 00:23:05,367
All the household rules

408
00:23:05,367 --> 00:23:06,833
were set by my grandma.

409
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:09,067
My grandpa didn't dare to say a word.

410
00:23:14,367 --> 00:23:14,967
Let's go.

411
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:22,867
Get out of the car.

412
00:23:23,167 --> 00:23:23,833
Wait for me a second.

413
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:24,667
Let me prepare.

414
00:23:24,767 --> 00:23:25,967
Please close the window for me.

415
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,000
What are you preparing for?

416
00:23:49,333 --> 00:23:49,867
How's this?

417
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:01,700
Remember

418
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:03,433
from the moment you step out of the car

419
00:24:03,667 --> 00:24:04,567
you're Wang Linlin.

420
00:24:05,233 --> 00:24:05,933
Got it.

421
00:24:05,933 --> 00:24:06,500
What's your name?

422
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:07,167
Wang Linlin.

423
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:11,333
It's not that I don't trust you

424
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:12,900
I'm just afraid you'll slip up.

425
00:24:13,333 --> 00:24:14,067
What's your name?

426
00:24:14,067 --> 00:24:14,667
Wang Linlin.

427
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:16,867
Just forget about the past.

428
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:18,300
Today is the day to move forward.

429
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,067
I'm 1.68 meters tall.

430
00:24:22,067 --> 00:24:23,133
I weigh 90 jin.

431
00:24:23,133 --> 00:24:24,833
I graduated from Changsha Media University.

432
00:24:25,067 --> 00:24:26,500
I grew up in Hunan.

433
00:24:26,500 --> 00:24:28,300
After graduation, I came to Nanwu.

434
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:28,933
We met

435
00:24:28,933 --> 00:24:31,167
at a classmate's birthday party.

436
00:24:31,167 --> 00:24:32,500
We've been together a year and a half

437
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:33,933
broken up twice.

438
00:24:33,933 --> 00:24:35,367
Once because you bought the wrong bag

439
00:24:35,367 --> 00:24:36,867
and once because you overslept

440
00:24:36,867 --> 00:24:37,567
and didn't pick me up.

441
00:24:37,567 --> 00:24:38,533
The first breakup lasted two days

442
00:24:38,533 --> 00:24:39,533
and the second lasted three and a half days.

443
00:24:39,533 --> 00:24:40,400
Later, you bought the right bag

444
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:41,367
and I forgave you.

445
00:24:44,233 --> 00:24:45,167
Where did you get all this from?

446
00:24:46,300 --> 00:24:48,000
I've been reading your posts on Weibo.

447
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,000
I've also read your Moments

448
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,333
through Dian's WeChat.

449
00:24:53,067 --> 00:24:54,700
Honestly, it's really hard to keep anything private

450
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:55,533
these days.

451
00:24:55,533 --> 00:24:56,167
Should I

452
00:24:56,167 --> 00:24:57,367
block you guys from my Moments?

453
00:24:57,933 --> 00:24:58,433
What?

454
00:25:04,767 --> 00:25:05,367
Miss Wen.

455
00:25:07,900 --> 00:25:08,400
Morning.

456
00:25:08,633 --> 00:25:09,433
There's something for you.

457
00:25:11,100 --> 00:25:12,300
The lady who met you here last time

458
00:25:12,433 --> 00:25:13,400
dropped it off this morning.

459
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:14,900
Is she a relative of yours?

460
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:18,200
Thanks, Uncle Zhang.

461
00:25:18,233 --> 00:25:18,733
Alright.

462
00:25:23,667 --> 00:25:24,333
Don't mention it.

463
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:25,900
I've gained five pounds.

464
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:28,900
What are we having for lunch today?

465
00:25:30,433 --> 00:25:31,400
Today is the Lantern Festival.

466
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,100
How about

467
00:25:32,100 --> 00:25:33,367
we go get some sweet dumplings?

468
00:25:33,533 --> 00:25:34,100
That sounds good.

469
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:35,400
Let's go to the tea shop first.

470
00:25:35,567 --> 00:25:36,067
Let's go.

471
00:25:40,667 --> 00:25:41,167
Let's go.

472
00:25:47,733 --> 00:25:51,600
[Zhao Yuandong]

473
00:25:54,233 --> 00:25:54,867
Jiang

474
00:25:55,133 --> 00:25:56,400
did you get the red envelope?

475
00:25:58,967 --> 00:25:59,933
I don't know

476
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:01,700
where you are living in Nanwu.

477
00:26:01,933 --> 00:26:03,833
And you said you'd be working during the Spring Festival.

478
00:26:04,567 --> 00:26:06,400
So, I sent it directly to your workplace.

479
00:26:11,900 --> 00:26:12,767
You probably think

480
00:26:12,767 --> 00:26:14,300
with WeChat red envelopes being so convenient

481
00:26:14,300 --> 00:26:15,567
why go through the trouble of delivering it?

482
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:17,233
I just prefer

483
00:26:17,633 --> 00:26:19,400
handing out the red envelope in person.

484
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:21,633
I always think about seeing you in person.

485
00:26:35,033 --> 00:26:36,400
[To Wen Yifan]

486
00:26:37,967 --> 00:26:42,067
[Jiang, wishing you great fortune and good health. - Mom]

487
00:26:42,067 --> 00:26:42,900
Jiang

488
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:45,100
Happy New Year!

489
00:26:45,867 --> 00:26:46,900
What do you want?

490
00:26:47,333 --> 00:26:48,367
Go buy it yourself.

491
00:26:49,533 --> 00:26:50,933
I don't want anything.

492
00:26:51,933 --> 00:26:53,433
I just want you to get better soon.

493
00:26:54,733 --> 00:26:55,967
I'm fine.

494
00:26:57,167 --> 00:26:57,900
Take it.

495
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:08,500
It's the New Year.

496
00:27:12,633 --> 00:27:13,233
I want

497
00:27:13,233 --> 00:27:15,100
to make a New Year wish.

498
00:27:16,333 --> 00:27:17,333
May I?

499
00:27:19,567 --> 00:27:20,667
I want

500
00:27:22,233 --> 00:27:23,867
to take you out for another day of fun.

501
00:27:25,667 --> 00:27:26,733
Anywhere is fine.

502
00:27:28,167 --> 00:27:29,067
Just one day.

503
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:32,433
You've already taken me to many places.

504
00:27:33,433 --> 00:27:35,967
Then, it's your turn to take us out.

505
00:27:37,433 --> 00:27:38,233
When you get better

506
00:27:38,233 --> 00:27:39,933
I'll take you wherever you want to go.

507
00:27:41,100 --> 00:27:41,700
Okay.

508
00:27:42,100 --> 00:27:43,967
Ask your mom where she wants to go.

509
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:46,933
You need to make her happy.

510
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:51,267
[Jiang, wishing you great fortune and good health. - Mom]

511
00:28:02,667 --> 00:28:03,267
Hello

512
00:28:03,633 --> 00:28:04,367
Jiang.

513
00:28:06,567 --> 00:28:07,900
I've received your red envelope.

514
00:28:08,967 --> 00:28:09,767
Thanks, Mom.

515
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:11,000
I'm glad you received it.

516
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:12,500
It's just a small token from me.

517
00:28:13,133 --> 00:28:14,000
Some day...

518
00:28:16,233 --> 00:28:18,167
when you're free

519
00:28:19,100 --> 00:28:20,000
I'll come see you.

520
00:28:24,533 --> 00:28:25,300
Great.

521
00:28:25,967 --> 00:28:27,333
I've been wanting to see you for a while.

522
00:28:27,433 --> 00:28:29,300
I'll make you something delicious.

523
00:28:29,767 --> 00:28:30,900
Let's do it this weekend.

524
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:32,400
What time do you usually finish work?

525
00:28:32,900 --> 00:28:34,533
How about you come over after work today?

526
00:28:36,233 --> 00:28:37,333
Are you in a rush?

527
00:28:40,633 --> 00:28:41,833
Xin, come here.

528
00:28:42,167 --> 00:28:43,833
My mom bought an extra bowl of sweet dumplings.

529
00:28:43,833 --> 00:28:44,667
Let's eat together.

530
00:28:44,867 --> 00:28:45,433
Coming.

531
00:28:51,900 --> 00:28:53,733
Alright, see you after work today.

532
00:28:53,933 --> 00:28:55,267
Okay, I'll wait for you.

533
00:28:55,900 --> 00:28:56,533
See you at home.

534
00:29:07,133 --> 00:29:07,767
Oh my.

535
00:29:16,333 --> 00:29:17,133
Come on over.

536
00:29:21,933 --> 00:29:22,900
Linlin, right?

537
00:29:23,900 --> 00:29:24,667
Sit next to me.

538
00:29:26,633 --> 00:29:27,167
Okay.

539
00:29:32,367 --> 00:29:33,133
Uncle Ma

540
00:29:33,500 --> 00:29:34,300
time to eat!

541
00:29:34,500 --> 00:29:35,500
Okay, I'm coming.

542
00:29:39,100 --> 00:29:40,667
Ma, sit here.

543
00:29:41,733 --> 00:29:42,867
But what about him?

544
00:29:42,933 --> 00:29:44,100
Just sit here.

545
00:29:59,067 --> 00:30:00,133
I'll go help Grandpa.

546
00:30:07,133 --> 00:30:07,733
Grandpa

547
00:30:07,867 --> 00:30:08,567
let me help you.

548
00:30:10,067 --> 00:30:10,733
Grandpa

549
00:30:11,633 --> 00:30:13,733
was Grandma happy since she came back this time?

550
00:30:17,300 --> 00:30:18,133
She's okay, I guess.

551
00:30:18,767 --> 00:30:19,767
But today

552
00:30:19,767 --> 00:30:21,167
you brought your girlfriend.

553
00:30:21,167 --> 00:30:22,300
She'll be happy.

554
00:30:22,767 --> 00:30:23,700
Really?

555
00:30:23,867 --> 00:30:25,833
But her expression seems a bit off.

556
00:30:28,433 --> 00:30:29,100
Help me

557
00:30:29,100 --> 00:30:30,233
serve the dishes, quickly.

558
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:32,233
The dishes are ready.

559
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:35,433
Linlin

560
00:30:36,300 --> 00:30:37,667
you're in for a treat today.

561
00:30:38,067 --> 00:30:39,200
My cooking

562
00:30:39,367 --> 00:30:41,300
is top-notch in Nanwu!

563
00:30:41,733 --> 00:30:42,900
Grandpa is amazing.

564
00:30:42,967 --> 00:30:44,833
Then I'll definitely enjoy this meal to the fullest!

565
00:30:44,867 --> 00:30:45,400
Good.

566
00:30:45,967 --> 00:30:46,667
An

567
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:48,367
introduce her properly.

568
00:30:49,367 --> 00:30:50,833
Grandpa, Grandma, this is Zhong Siqiao.

569
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:54,333
Zhong Siqiao?

570
00:30:55,767 --> 00:30:56,433
She's...

571
00:30:56,833 --> 00:30:57,833
I am...

572
00:30:58,067 --> 00:30:59,400
living near a bridge

573
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:01,000
called Zhong Siqiao.

574
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:01,567
Exactly!

575
00:31:01,567 --> 00:31:02,567
My name is Wang Linlin.

576
00:31:02,567 --> 00:31:03,933
- Right. - Just call me Linlin.

577
00:31:05,433 --> 00:31:06,233
Ma

578
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:08,233
where's the Zhong Siqiao Bridge?

579
00:31:09,333 --> 00:31:10,067
It's newly built!

580
00:31:10,233 --> 00:31:11,100
- Right, newly built! - Newly built.

581
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:12,100
Newly built.

582
00:31:12,533 --> 00:31:13,533
Miss Wang

583
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:16,000
I've heard so much about you.

584
00:31:17,367 --> 00:31:18,233
Grandpa

585
00:31:18,500 --> 00:31:20,200
the dishes you made look so delicious.

586
00:31:20,200 --> 00:31:21,233
It's a shame they're cold.

587
00:31:21,233 --> 00:31:22,333
Let's eat quickly.

588
00:31:22,967 --> 00:31:24,000
Grandpa, please.

589
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,100
- Try it. - Come on.

590
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:26,733
Quick, try it.

591
00:31:26,833 --> 00:31:27,833
This is my grandpa's specialty

592
00:31:28,133 --> 00:31:28,967
Kung Pao Shrimp.

593
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,233
This is white wine.

594
00:31:41,233 --> 00:31:42,000
I'll go get some tissues.

595
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:42,633
Are you alright?

596
00:31:42,633 --> 00:31:43,767
Quick!

597
00:31:46,100 --> 00:31:47,700
Linlin is from Hunan.

598
00:31:48,200 --> 00:31:50,400
Grandpa thinks Hunan folks love spicy food

599
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:51,733
so he added a lot of chili.

600
00:31:52,833 --> 00:31:55,733
But you, being from Hunan, need to keep up!

601
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:57,167
Right.

602
00:31:57,167 --> 00:31:58,633
Here, cheers!

603
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:05,933
Move aside

604
00:32:06,367 --> 00:32:07,633
or it'll spill on you.

605
00:32:10,933 --> 00:32:11,433
Grandma

606
00:32:11,433 --> 00:32:12,700
let me help you with the washing.

607
00:32:12,700 --> 00:32:13,867
I'm good at washing cars.

608
00:32:15,300 --> 00:32:16,000
I'll help you.

609
00:32:28,933 --> 00:32:30,367
Is it okay in this cold weather?

610
00:32:30,433 --> 00:32:31,533
It's fine. It's not cold.

611
00:32:53,333 --> 00:32:54,067
Grandma

612
00:32:54,300 --> 00:32:55,633
these essential oils

613
00:32:55,633 --> 00:32:57,833
all have the function of refreshing.

614
00:32:57,867 --> 00:32:59,500
When get sleepy while driving

615
00:32:59,700 --> 00:33:00,667
you can sniff them

616
00:33:00,833 --> 00:33:02,900
apply them behind your ears, or on your neck.

617
00:33:02,967 --> 00:33:04,400
It'll immediately lift your spirits.

618
00:33:04,567 --> 00:33:06,067
You've studied this?

619
00:33:06,933 --> 00:33:08,833
I often use them when I work night shifts.

620
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,900
You have my grandson as your personal ATM

621
00:33:10,933 --> 00:33:12,900
why are you still working so hard?

622
00:33:16,533 --> 00:33:17,433
I know

623
00:33:17,933 --> 00:33:19,300
you're not Wang Linlin.

624
00:33:20,500 --> 00:33:22,500
I just searched it on the map app.

625
00:33:22,667 --> 00:33:23,700
There's no Zhong Siqiao Bridge

626
00:33:23,700 --> 00:33:25,967
around Nanwu at all.

627
00:33:26,367 --> 00:33:28,700
Since Zhong Siqiao isn't a bridge

628
00:33:28,933 --> 00:33:30,233
that must be your real name.

629
00:33:34,300 --> 00:33:35,400
Grandma

630
00:33:35,667 --> 00:33:38,300
you're really too smart.

631
00:33:38,700 --> 00:33:40,167
All you old and young ones

632
00:33:40,567 --> 00:33:42,367
don't tell me the truth.

633
00:33:50,133 --> 00:33:52,367
Grandma, don't be mad.

634
00:33:53,133 --> 00:33:53,933
We were wrong.

635
00:33:54,333 --> 00:33:55,833
But there's some good news.

636
00:33:56,167 --> 00:33:57,333
Su Haoan has broken up

637
00:33:57,333 --> 00:33:58,933
with the real Wang Linlin.

638
00:33:59,667 --> 00:34:01,000
He asked me to pretend to be his girlfriend

639
00:34:01,433 --> 00:34:03,333
just to get you home for the New Year reunion.

640
00:34:06,333 --> 00:34:08,833
I know what my grandson thought.

641
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:10,500
I don't blame you.

642
00:34:11,933 --> 00:34:14,300
But I am really curious.

643
00:34:14,300 --> 00:34:15,867
As a young girl

644
00:34:15,867 --> 00:34:17,133
you can wash cars

645
00:34:17,133 --> 00:34:18,500
install things

646
00:34:18,500 --> 00:34:20,100
and aren't afraid to walk barefoot.

647
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:21,700
What do you do for a living?

648
00:34:22,533 --> 00:34:24,767
I just help out with everything

649
00:34:24,967 --> 00:34:26,700
fixing things

650
00:34:26,900 --> 00:34:27,900
queuing for tickets

651
00:34:27,967 --> 00:34:29,200
talking to the elderly

652
00:34:29,200 --> 00:34:30,833
taking the elderly to see doctors, and more.

653
00:34:31,900 --> 00:34:33,300
Is there this kind of job?

654
00:34:33,300 --> 00:34:33,800
Yeah.

655
00:34:34,067 --> 00:34:35,100
I even have a service app.

656
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:38,367
There's a QR code on the business card.

657
00:34:38,900 --> 00:34:40,200
You can scan it and place an order.

658
00:34:40,300 --> 00:34:42,100
[Zhong Siqiao]
If you ever need any help

659
00:34:42,100 --> 00:34:42,967
you can find me.

660
00:34:42,967 --> 00:34:43,533
Great.

661
00:34:43,967 --> 00:34:45,433
I'll make sure my grandson

662
00:34:45,667 --> 00:34:46,733
gives you a good review.

663
00:34:47,067 --> 00:34:47,967
Thank you, Grandma.

664
00:34:48,233 --> 00:34:49,700
I'll continue helping you install it.

665
00:34:49,867 --> 00:34:50,867
There's a massage chair left.

666
00:35:00,300 --> 00:35:01,667
Jiang, you're here!

667
00:35:03,033 --> 00:35:04,200
No need to change shoes. Just come in and sit.

668
00:35:06,133 --> 00:35:07,533
Why are you dressed so lightly?

669
00:35:07,867 --> 00:35:08,833
Isn't it cold outside?

670
00:35:10,433 --> 00:35:11,267
This is for you.

671
00:35:12,533 --> 00:35:13,733
Sorry, I should've helped you with it.

672
00:35:13,733 --> 00:35:14,933
Come in and sit.

673
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:18,167
Come on, let's sit inside.

674
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:22,833
Isn't it cold outside?

675
00:35:22,833 --> 00:35:24,300
You're dressed too lightly.

676
00:35:30,567 --> 00:35:31,667
I'll go get you a cup of water.

677
00:35:36,667 --> 00:35:37,667
I didn't visit you before

678
00:35:38,667 --> 00:35:39,500
because I didn't want

679
00:35:39,500 --> 00:35:40,433
to disturb you.

680
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:43,433
I haven't seen you for so long.

681
00:35:44,167 --> 00:35:45,100
I'm a bit excited.

682
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:47,833
Here, drink some water.

683
00:35:48,500 --> 00:35:49,300
Warm up your hands.

684
00:35:56,100 --> 00:35:57,300
Look at you

685
00:35:58,500 --> 00:35:59,900
you've got so thin.

686
00:36:01,833 --> 00:36:03,667
Haven't you been eating properly?

687
00:36:04,567 --> 00:36:06,100
If you want anything to eat, just tell me

688
00:36:06,100 --> 00:36:07,233
I'll come over and make it for you.

689
00:36:07,867 --> 00:36:08,533
No need.

690
00:36:10,100 --> 00:36:11,267
I'm eating well.

691
00:36:12,167 --> 00:36:14,267
Besides, I have a roommate. It's not convenient.

692
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:20,133
I still have things cooking in the kitchen.

693
00:36:20,933 --> 00:36:22,300
Knowing you were coming

694
00:36:22,300 --> 00:36:24,067
I made sweet dumplings specially for you.

695
00:36:24,900 --> 00:36:27,767
You loved hot sweet dumplings when you were little.

696
00:36:28,733 --> 00:36:29,433
Today

697
00:36:29,433 --> 00:36:30,533
is the 15th day of the New Year.

698
00:36:31,367 --> 00:36:33,233
This is when the family should reunite.

699
00:36:37,667 --> 00:36:38,300
Here.

700
00:36:39,433 --> 00:36:40,567
Hurry, eat it while it's hot.

701
00:36:49,367 --> 00:36:50,433
Jiang

702
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:52,000
you've grown up

703
00:36:53,167 --> 00:36:54,300
and looked even prettier now.

704
00:36:56,267 --> 00:36:58,400
Why don't I see Uncle Zheng?

705
00:36:59,000 --> 00:36:59,900
And where's Zheng Kejia?

706
00:37:00,867 --> 00:37:01,600
They

707
00:37:02,167 --> 00:37:03,567
took her grandma back to their hometown.

708
00:37:03,867 --> 00:37:05,167
No wonder you insisted I come over today.

709
00:37:09,500 --> 00:37:10,367
Mom.

710
00:37:11,267 --> 00:37:11,933
Mom.

711
00:37:12,333 --> 00:37:13,133
Xin!

712
00:37:13,233 --> 00:37:14,933
Why did you come down?

713
00:37:16,967 --> 00:37:17,667
Who is he?

714
00:37:20,067 --> 00:37:21,600
I told you last time

715
00:37:22,067 --> 00:37:23,900
I wanted to introduce someone to you.

716
00:37:24,833 --> 00:37:25,700
This is him.

717
00:37:25,700 --> 00:37:27,233
He's the son of me and your Uncle Zheng.

718
00:37:28,067 --> 00:37:29,233
He's your real brother.

719
00:37:30,900 --> 00:37:31,833
His name is Zheng Kexin.

720
00:37:37,967 --> 00:37:40,333
Mom, who is she?

721
00:37:40,967 --> 00:37:42,500
She's your sister, Jiang.

722
00:37:42,733 --> 00:37:44,133
She's also my child.

723
00:37:44,133 --> 00:37:45,100
She's your real sister.

724
00:37:45,567 --> 00:37:48,067
Why didn't you mention her to me?

725
00:37:50,367 --> 00:37:51,500
She didn't mention you to me either.

726
00:37:53,767 --> 00:37:55,167
Let me explain.

727
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:56,933
I was quite old

728
00:37:57,067 --> 00:37:58,767
when I had him.

729
00:37:58,867 --> 00:38:00,600
I even had a miscarriage before...

730
00:38:00,600 --> 00:38:01,233
Xin!

731
00:38:05,300 --> 00:38:06,067
Xin!

732
00:38:11,533 --> 00:38:12,967
Who's this?

733
00:38:13,767 --> 00:38:15,233
Isn't that Jiang?

734
00:38:15,333 --> 00:38:16,900
How many years has it been since we last met?

735
00:38:16,900 --> 00:38:17,900
Let me take a good look at you!

736
00:38:17,900 --> 00:38:18,667
She was embarrassed to see you.

737
00:38:18,833 --> 00:38:20,333
What's embarrassing about that?

738
00:38:20,333 --> 00:38:21,700
Jiang is not an outsider.

739
00:38:21,700 --> 00:38:22,333
Come on

740
00:38:22,900 --> 00:38:24,600
let me take a good look at you.

741
00:38:25,967 --> 00:38:27,067
Look at you

742
00:38:27,267 --> 00:38:28,267
you're so ungrateful.

743
00:38:28,267 --> 00:38:30,133
You studied out of town for years

744
00:38:30,133 --> 00:38:31,833
and never came back to see me

745
00:38:31,833 --> 00:38:32,600
honestly.

746
00:38:32,700 --> 00:38:33,567
Why is she here?

747
00:38:34,700 --> 00:38:35,700
It's a coincidence.

748
00:38:35,700 --> 00:38:37,567
Your aunt just happened to come over.

749
00:38:37,833 --> 00:38:38,833
Jiang, don't act like that.

750
00:38:44,967 --> 00:38:45,500
Jiang

751
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:47,867
what are you doing now?

752
00:38:50,267 --> 00:38:50,833
By the way

753
00:38:50,833 --> 00:38:52,500
my head hurt earlier, and my throat's sore.

754
00:38:52,500 --> 00:38:54,300
Go get me some medicine.

755
00:38:54,300 --> 00:38:54,933
Okay.

756
00:38:54,933 --> 00:38:55,667
I'll get it for you.

757
00:39:00,933 --> 00:39:01,533
By the way

758
00:39:01,833 --> 00:39:02,733
I have to tell you something.

759
00:39:02,900 --> 00:39:04,300
Your cousin Wen Ming

760
00:39:04,500 --> 00:39:05,933
is getting married this year.

761
00:39:11,100 --> 00:39:11,833
Congratulations.

762
00:39:13,567 --> 00:39:14,767
What's so great about it?

763
00:39:14,767 --> 00:39:15,667
They got the certificate

764
00:39:15,867 --> 00:39:17,600
but they haven't settled on the wedding house yet.

765
00:39:18,867 --> 00:39:19,500
So what?

766
00:39:22,333 --> 00:39:22,933
You see

767
00:39:23,300 --> 00:39:24,067
before

768
00:39:24,167 --> 00:39:26,367
we took care of you for so long.

769
00:39:26,700 --> 00:39:27,933
You should at least help him.

770
00:39:27,933 --> 00:39:29,667
After all, you're just a girl.

771
00:39:29,667 --> 00:39:30,967
You don't have many expenses.

772
00:39:30,967 --> 00:39:31,567
Right?

773
00:39:34,933 --> 00:39:35,567
Aunt

774
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:37,300
I knew a lady lately.

775
00:39:37,300 --> 00:39:38,600
She's very rich.

776
00:39:38,833 --> 00:39:40,067
She's not very old

777
00:39:40,367 --> 00:39:41,367
two years younger than you.

778
00:39:42,067 --> 00:39:42,667
How about this?

779
00:39:43,133 --> 00:39:44,600
I could introduce her to Wen Ming.

780
00:39:44,967 --> 00:39:46,400
That way, you won't have to worry about the wedding house.

781
00:39:46,500 --> 00:39:47,567
What nonsense are you spouting?

782
00:39:51,300 --> 00:39:52,500
That's the only way I can talk to you.

783
00:39:53,500 --> 00:39:54,933
If I knew you were such an ungrateful person

784
00:39:55,067 --> 00:39:56,567
I shouldn't have taken care of you back then!

785
00:39:56,967 --> 00:39:57,767
What's wrong, Jiang?

786
00:39:57,833 --> 00:39:58,333
I am going

787
00:39:58,367 --> 00:39:59,367
to cook for you.

788
00:40:02,300 --> 00:40:03,567
I won't come here anymore.

789
00:40:16,300 --> 00:40:17,767
This is the last time I'll be here.

790
00:40:18,333 --> 00:40:19,333
All of you people...

791
00:40:21,667 --> 00:40:22,900
I don't want to see any of you again.

792
00:40:24,767 --> 00:40:25,600
I came for my dad's sake.

793
00:40:26,333 --> 00:40:27,700
Before my dad passed away, he told me

794
00:40:27,700 --> 00:40:28,667
to take good care of you.

795
00:40:29,400 --> 00:40:31,100
I have no choice but to follow his will.

796
00:40:32,767 --> 00:40:34,300
Just consider it like I died with my dad.

797
00:40:37,900 --> 00:40:39,000
You're talking nonsense.

798
00:40:39,133 --> 00:40:40,367
Dad didn't die.

799
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:45,167
Xin

800
00:40:45,700 --> 00:40:47,533
her dad isn't your dad.

801
00:40:47,867 --> 00:40:48,767
Don't worry.

802
00:41:21,967 --> 00:41:26,667
♪Once again, I hear the farewell from that day♪

803
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:33,967
♪Tears fall as the memory replays...♪

804
00:41:39,433 --> 00:41:40,100
Be careful.

805
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:47,267
♪Wishing for a better chapter ahead♪

806
00:41:48,733 --> 00:41:52,667
♪The answers of time♪

807
00:41:53,433 --> 00:41:56,133
[I'm in the courtyard. Come join me?]
♪Should be handed in a bit late♪

808
00:41:56,800 --> 00:42:03,000
♪The journey ahead should keep extending♪

809
00:42:05,967 --> 00:42:11,033
♪I fear you might be a little late♪

810
00:42:12,633 --> 00:42:18,067
♪Leaving me lost in the crowd...♪

811
00:42:18,100 --> 00:42:19,100
It's the last day of the New Year holiday.

812
00:42:19,733 --> 00:42:20,333
I bought too many.

813
00:42:20,667 --> 00:42:21,400
Help me light some?

814
00:42:26,633 --> 00:42:32,200
♪Searching for you is destined to be a painful journey♪

815
00:42:33,200 --> 00:42:38,867
♪I'd rather you come a bit later♪

816
00:42:39,967 --> 00:42:45,533
♪The things we lose will be returned in the end...♪

817
00:42:50,533 --> 00:42:51,733
Jiang, do you want to try this?

818
00:42:52,167 --> 00:42:53,133
Jiang, try it.

819
00:42:53,133 --> 00:42:54,267
Light it up, come on.

820
00:42:54,267 --> 00:42:55,067
I'll light it.

821
00:42:55,167 --> 00:42:55,933
Good.

822
00:42:59,400 --> 00:43:00,100
That's it?

823
00:43:00,500 --> 00:43:01,300
Here it goes.

824
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:04,267
Alright, let's watch it.

825
00:43:04,867 --> 00:43:06,400
Big fireworks.

826
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:07,000
Yeah.

827
00:43:07,367 --> 00:43:09,367
What shape is this?

828
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:11,400
A triangle.

829
00:43:15,167 --> 00:43:20,633
♪Maybe forgetting some expectations...♪

830
00:43:20,633 --> 00:43:24,767
[Episode 7]
[A Secret... that Can't be Kept]

831
00:43:36,833 --> 00:43:37,567
Sir

832
00:43:37,900 --> 00:43:40,567
[The story is not over yet...]
did we make noise and bother you?

833
00:43:41,333 --> 00:43:43,333
We'll leave once these fireworks are done.

834
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:46,933
What time is it?

835
00:43:47,400 --> 00:43:49,900
Forget it. I want to go home now.

836
00:43:51,400 --> 00:43:52,600
Alright, let's go.

837
00:43:54,067 --> 00:43:54,667
Wait a minute.

838
00:44:00,700 --> 00:44:02,067
How about selling these remaining ones

839
00:44:02,067 --> 00:44:02,933
to me?

840
00:44:03,767 --> 00:44:04,533
Really?

841
00:44:04,700 --> 00:44:05,700
I'll pay you

842
00:44:05,900 --> 00:44:06,933
double the price.

843
00:44:08,933 --> 00:44:09,900
That's great!

844
00:44:21,833 --> 00:44:23,167
♪Even the strongest heart♪

845
00:44:23,333 --> 00:44:25,000
♪Can waver♪

846
00:44:25,233 --> 00:44:28,433
♪And doubt its fire♪

847
00:44:28,667 --> 00:44:30,333
♪But you never lost faith in me♪

848
00:44:30,333 --> 00:44:32,000
♪In every battle, every dream I chased♪

849
00:44:32,200 --> 00:44:34,867
♪There is meaning in every step I made♪

850
00:44:35,733 --> 00:44:41,667
♪Through the storm, through the endless night♪

851
00:44:42,033 --> 00:44:43,667
